cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SI 

The paper deals with coalition games, which are a subfield of game theory, and specifically focuses on the interaction graph model. This makes cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Making) the most likely sub-category. The paper also heavily relies on graph theory, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses LP formulations and their integrality gaps, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
